  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lifesaving Multi-Sectoral Assistance in Dignified Shelter, Essential Household Items and Water, Hygiene and Sanitation for the Most Vulnerable Displaced Persons in Lac Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The urgent needs for an integrated approach to shelter and essential non-food items (NFI) and water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) for displaced populations in Chad&#x2019;s Lac province remain high. In 2021, the Humanitarian Response Plan was only 30% funded, leaving many gaps in the assistance to populations affected by the humanitarian crisis unfolding in the province. In November 2021, more than 744,000 people were still waiting to receive shelter and NFI assistance. Similarly, the WASH Cluster counted in 2021, more than 140,000 targeted people had not yet been reached with WASH assistance. In addition to former unassisted internally displaced persons (IDPs), new IDPs are not systematically served even though they have lost everything. These shortcomings have catastrophic consequences for people who remain without the assistance that helps preserve their dignity and safety. Therefore, IOM through an integrated approach, is providing Shelter, NFI, and WASH assistance to meet the basic needs of displaced populations and contribute to their protection and dignity.</narrative>
  </description>
